title: For Sale:  NIB Glock 19 9mm 15rd Gen-3 not 17 26 23 Gen-4
postcontent: New Glock 19, Generation 3, Subcompact Pistol chambered in 9mm. Glock first released the revolutionary model 17 in 1982. At that time it was one of the most futuristic designs on the market and incorporated little seen features such as lightweight polymer frame and a high-capacity double stack magazine. The model 17 also served as the first introduction to Glock's Safe Action Pistol concept. This revolutionary design featured 3 integral safety systems to ensure operator safety, but did not include an external, manual safety that might impede unpracticed or unfamiliar shooters. Since the 80s Glock has come a long way in improving and expanding on this design and they now have guns ranging from optimized competitive target shooting guns to concealed carry weapons. The Glock 19 is a compact model and is the most popular Glock model in production. It features a 4 inch hexagonally rifled barrel that increases weapon service life, decreases fouling, simplifies cleaning and improves muzzle velocity over a traditionally rifled barrel. The model 19 measures in at 7.36 inches is length and 1.18 inches in width, making it an ideal choice for a do-everything pistol. The Glock 19 ships from the factory with 2 15 round magazines but can also accept higher capacity magazines ranging from 17 rounds to the extended Glock 33 round mag. A double-action, striker-fired operating system is used to provide the ultimate in safety as well as a short, crisp trigger reset. Glock has earned a reputation for making some of the most reliable pistols on the market. This is due to their simplistic design, which utilizes only 35 components including the magazine and sights. This design ensures that there are no complicated assemblies to break at the worst possible time. Whether you are looking for the perfect carry gun, a home defense pistol, a target pistol for shooters with smaller hands or just want to own one of the best pistols ever made, this Glock 19 is perfect for you.

title: For Sale:  NIB Glock 19 9mm 15rd Gen-3 not 17 26 23 Gen-4
postcontent: New Glock 19, Generation 3, Subcompact Pistol chambered in 9mm. Glock first released the revolutionary model 17 in 1982. At that time it was one of the most futuristic designs on the market and incorporated little seen features such as lightweight polymer frame and a high-capacity double stack magazine. The model 17 also served as the first introduction to Glock's Safe Action Pistol concept. This revolutionary design featured 3 integral safety systems to ensure operator safety, but did not include an external, manual safety that might impede unpracticed or unfamiliar shooters. Since the 80s Glock has come a long way in improving and expanding on this design and they now have guns ranging from optimized competitive target shooting guns to concealed carry weapons. The Glock 19 is a compact model and is the most popular Glock model in production. It features a 4 inch hexagonally rifled barrel that increases weapon service life, decreases fouling, simplifies cleaning and improves muzzle velocity over a traditionally rifled barrel. The model 19 measures in at 7.36 inches is length and 1.18 inches in width, making it an ideal choice for a do-everything pistol. The Glock 19 ships from the factory with 2 15 round magazines but can also accept higher capacity magazines ranging from 17 rounds to the extended Glock 33 round mag. A double-action, striker-fired operating system is used to provide the ultimate in safety as well as a short, crisp trigger reset. Glock has earned a reputation for making some of the most reliable pistols on the market. This is due to their simplistic design, which utilizes only 35 components including the magazine and sights. This design ensures that there are no complicated assemblies to break at the worst possible time. Whether you are looking for the perfect carry gun, a home defense pistol, a target pistol for shooters with smaller hands or just want to own one of the best pistols ever made, this Glock 19 is perfect for you.

postcontent:
I got a Chinese model sks. I don't know much about these but from my research its an early 1956 model from factory 26. According to the serial number it was done while the Russians were still supervising the Chinese wile making these. Which is what they call the Sino-Soviet style SKS. So this gun is about as early as they come from china. Has all the clues to verify this. The serial number, which is I9211. One letter then 4 numbers indicating russian style. All the parts that are supposed to be machined instead of stamped steal are machined. The barrel is threaded instead of pin on. the bayonet is blade style instead of spiked. bolt has been replaced. (serial # is different) all other numbers match. not sure if stock is original.  receiver and mechanicals still covered in cosmoline. this gun is in great shape. I don't know much about these so make me a cash offer or id be willing to trade for a complete 6.8 spc upper with at least an 18" barrel for my ar-15. complete as in bolt, carrier, ready to pin on and shoot. call/text (prefer text) REDACTED
